Via config file Edit with your favourite editor:
~/.jupyter/lab/user-settings/@jupyterlab/shortcuts-extension/shortcuts.jupyterlab-settings Via web interface Settings -&gt; Advanced Settings Editor -&gt; Keyboard Shortcuts
Example to use Shift+D to restart and run all cells { &#34;shortcuts&#34;:[ { &#34;command&#34;:&#34;runmenu:restart-and-run-all&#34;, &#34;keys&#34;:[ &#34;Shift D&#34; ], &#34;selector&#34;:&#34;[data-jp-code-runner]&#34; } ] }
